<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8">
  <!-- Header -->
  <section>
    <h1 class="py-6 text-xl font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Use YouCongress from ChatGPT
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      You can connect YouCongress to
      <a href="https://chatgpt.com" class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">
        ChatGPT
      </a>
      as an MCP app or connector to find sourced quotes and policies on AI governance, impact on jobs, etc.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      No coding or terminal commands needed. You just need ChatGPT developer mode enabled for your account or workspace.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="py-4 text-lg font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Step 1 - Enable developer mode
    </h2>
    <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-lg list-decimal pl-6">
      <li>
        Open
        <a
          href="https://chatgpt.com"
          class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
        >
          chatgpt.com
        </a>
        and open <strong>Settings</strong>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Go to <strong>Apps &amp; Connectors</strong>, then <strong>Advanced settings</strong>
        at the bottom of the page.
      </li>
      <li>
        Turn on <strong>Developer mode</strong>. If your organization disables it, ask your workspace admin to allow it.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="py-4 text-lg font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Step 2 - Create the YouCongress connector
    </h2>
    <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-lg list-decimal pl-6">
      <li>
        In ChatGPT, go to <strong>Settings</strong>
        -> <strong>Apps &amp; Connectors</strong>
        or <strong>Connectors</strong>, then click <strong>Create</strong>.
      </li>
      <li>
        For the name, use <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">YouCongress</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        For the description, use something like
        <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">
          Search sourced quotes and policy proposals from YouCongress.
        </code>
      </li>
      <li>
        In the connector URL field, paste:
        <div class="mt-2 flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-gray-100 border border-gray-200">
          <pre class="flex-1 text-sm overflow-x-auto m-0"><code id="chatgpt-mcp-url" class="block px-3 py-2">https://youcongress.org/mcp</code></pre>
          <button
            type="button"
            class="px-3 py-2 shrink-0 text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-800 transition-colors focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-blue-500 border-l border-gray-200"
            data-copy-target="chatgpt-mcp-url"
            aria-label="Copy URL"
          >
            <span class="sr-only">Copy URL</span>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              role="img"
              aria-hidden="true"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.6"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
            >
              <rect x="9" y="9" width="11" height="11" rx="2" />
              <path d="M5 15V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10" />
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        Click <strong>Create</strong>. If the connection succeeds, ChatGPT will show the tools YouCongress advertises.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="py-4 text-lg font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Step 3 - Use YouCongress in a chat
    </h2>
    <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-lg list-decimal pl-6">
      <li>Open a new ChatGPT conversation.</li>
      <li>
        Click the <strong>+</strong>
        button near the message composer, choose <strong>More</strong>, then choose <strong>YouCongress</strong>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Try one of the prompts below. If ChatGPT asks for permission to use a YouCongress tool, review the request and allow it.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <.prompt_examples>
      <:intro>
        Example prompts:
      </:intro>
      <:permission_notice>
        ChatGPT may decide when to use YouCongress automatically based on your app permissions. Mention "YouCongress" in your prompt if you want to make the tool choice explicit.
      </:permission_notice>
    </.prompt_examples>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="py-4 text-lg font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Tips
    </h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-lg list-disc pl-6">
      <li>
        If you want write access for creating or editing data, log in to YouCongress, create an API key in Settings, and use
        <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">
          https://youcongress.org/mcp?key=YOUR_API_KEY
        </code>
        as the connector URL.
      </li>
      <li>
        For any other MCP-capable assistant, use the same server URL: <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">https://youcongress.org/mcp</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        For a full list of available tools, see the <a
          href="/mcp-tools"
          class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
        >MCP Tools reference</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
<!-- CTA -->
  <div class="text-center pb-8">
    <%= if @current_user do %>
      <a
        href="/settings"
        class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors duration-200 shadow-md"
      >
        Get Your API Key in Settings
      </a>
    <% else %>
      <.link
        href={~p"/log_in"}
        method="get"
        class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors duration-200 shadow-md"
      >
        Log In to Get Started
      </.link>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
